"{\"uid\": \"rferl.org-a-russia-olympics-figure-skating-doping-32798270.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Share  Share  Print  The International Skating Union (ISU) has demoted the Russian figure-skating team that competed in the Beijing Olympics in 2022 from gold to bronze because of the disqualification of Russian teen skater Kamila Valiyeva for a doping offense.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 47, \"end\": 52, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999975675564, \"rank\": 1.6745486380008437e-09, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 75, \"end\": 82, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997633338759006, \"rank\": 0.0002362407940874553, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997633338759006, \"rank\": 0.0002362407940874553, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kamila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On January 29, the Swiss-based Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS)ruledin favor of a four-year suspension for Valiyeva, effective from December 2021, for doping.\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A day later, the ISUsaidthat without the points Valiyeva scored in the team event, Russia was being moved down to third place, pushing the United States into the top spot, followed by Japan.Valiyeva, now 17, tested positive for the banned substance trimetazidine in December 2021, with the results only becoming known after her Olympics victory.\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999991141548266, \"rank\": 8.613669544399586e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7000975813206759, \"rank\": 0.40502097027550144, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trimetazidine, a heart medication, is a banned substance, as it can boost endurance.Since the test results came right after the team event, medals were never awarded as a protracted legal battle over the case commenced.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trimetazidine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Trimetazidine\", \"types\": [\"Q8386\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trimetazidine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trimetazidine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ISU welcomes the decision of CAS and firmly maintains its position that the protection of clean athletes and the fight against doping are of the highest priority and will persist in the ongoing effort to uphold the integrity of fair competition and the well-being of athletes,\\\" the skating body said.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8773062662599316e-55, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ISU is in close contact with the International Olympic Committee (IOC) and the relevant ISU member federations in regard to the implementation of this decision.\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1390, \"end\": 1393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It added that the decision meant Vasilyeva was disqualified from her fourth-place showing in the women's singles event in Beijing, and from her first-place finish at the European Championships in 2022.The Russian Olympic Committee (ROC) said on January 30 it would appeal the ISU decision to strip it of an Olympic gold medal, stressing that its lawyers were preparing to contest the decision.\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8854955695178156, \"rank\": 0.08741914624881897, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.999975634043399, \"rank\": 2.43665504044507e-05, \"text\": \"Russian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9991151532576265, \"rank\": 0.0008856303897000729, \"text\": \"ROC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1739, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our position is based on the fact that due to the ISU's existing and applicable regulations, consequences of the decision to impose sanctions on an individual athlete, in this case Kamila Valiyeva, cannot be grounds for a revision of the results of the team tournament.\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1907, \"end\": 1910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our legal standpoint is also based on existing precedents in CAS practice,\\\" the ROCsaidin a statement.Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov said Russia should use \\\"any opportunities to challenge\\\" the decision and \\\"defend our athletes' rights.\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8773062662599316e-55, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dmitry_Peskov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dmitry Peskov\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dmitry_Peskov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dmitry_Peskov\"}, {\"begin\": 2266, \"end\": 2272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999991141548266, \"rank\": 8.613669544399586e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"\\\"We do not agree with these decisions -- neither with the decision of the court, nor with the decision of the federation.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We do not accept them,\\\" Peskov said, adding that the Russian skating team \\\"will always remain as champions for us, no matter what sort of decision they make there.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2539, \"end\": 2546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997633338759006, \"rank\": 0.0002362407940874553, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Russian athletes have been mired in doping scandals for the past decade after revelations of a state-backed system across many sports when the country hosted the 2014 Olympics in Sochi.\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997633338759006, \"rank\": 0.0002362407940874553, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9905851574789916, \"rank\": 0.009504324236769165, \"text\": \"Sochi\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An investigation into the issue led to Russian athletes being forced to prove they were \\\"clean\\\" and they had to compete as neutrals under a Russian Olympic Committee banner -- they were banned from using the Russian name, flag, or anthem -- in subsequent Games as part of IOC sanctions.\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2876, \"end\": 2883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997633338759006, \"rank\": 0.0002362407940874553, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2977, \"end\": 3002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.999975634043399, \"rank\": 2.43665504044507e-05, \"text\": \"Russian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2977, \"end\": 3002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.999975634043399, \"rank\": 2.43665504044507e-05, \"text\": \"Russian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997633338759006, \"rank\": 0.0002362407940874553, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3109, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.766724388511728e-46, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RFE/RL's Russian Service\\u00a0is a multi-platform alternative to Russian state-controlled media, providing audiences in the Russian Federation with informed and accurate news, analysis, and opinion.\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3125, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RFE/RL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty\"}, {\"begin\": 3134, \"end\": 3149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News_Russian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian Service\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News_Russian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News_Russian\"}, {\"begin\": 3185, \"end\": 3215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_media_in_Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian state-controlled media\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_media_in_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_media_in_Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9711985098751157, \"rank\": 0.018546958241789556, \"text\": \"Russian Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RFE/RL has been declared an \\\"undesirable organization\\\" by the Russian government.\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RFE/RL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty\"}, {\"begin\": 3384, \"end\": 3402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9996367282581993, \"rank\": 0.00036340375050096155, \"text\": \"Russian government\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are in Russia or the Russia-controlled parts of Ukraine and hold a Russian passport or are a stateless person residing permanently in Russia or the Russia-controlled parts of Ukraine, please note that you could face fines or imprisonment for sharing, liking, commenting on, or saving our content, or for contacting us.\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3419, \"end\": 3425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999991141548266, \"rank\": 8.613669544399586e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3460, \"end\": 3467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999779429347, \"rank\": 2.1977188879298688e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 3479, \"end\": 3495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_passport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian passport\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_passport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_passport\"}, {\"begin\": 3546, \"end\": 3552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999991141548266, \"rank\": 8.613669544399586e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3587, \"end\": 3594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999779429347, \"rank\": 2.1977188879298688e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/